hey i'm working on this embedded c++ project for an automotive sensor module and i'm running into a weird issue. the system runs fine for a few hours but then we hit a hard fault because we run out of heap memory. i've looked through the main loop but i can't find where the allocation isn't being freed. 

here is a snippet of the telemetry processing part. can you help me figure out a systematic way to track down where the memory is leaking?

```cpp
void process_telemetry(const uint8_t* raw_data, size_t len) {
    // Allocate buffer for incoming packet
    uint8_t* buffer = new uint8_t[len];
    memcpy(buffer, raw_data, len);

    // Process packet...
    if (parse_header(buffer) != SUCCESS) {
        // Log error and return
        log_error("header parse failed");
        return; 
    }

    // If parsing passes, pass to async worker
    dispatch_to_worker(buffer, len);
}
```
it seems like it happens more when the sensor hits high frequency. any ideas?

